WEBVTT

00:04.421 --> 00:06.089
(DISTORTED WHINNYING)

00:08.050 --> 00:09.718
(NEIGHING)

00:12.304 --> 00:13.972
(INDISTINCT CHATTERING)

00:14.389 --> 00:16.934
Gentlemen, I want you
to meet my daughters,

00:17.434 --> 00:19.061
Marie Louise Pauline,

00:19.144 --> 00:20.687
Marie Louise Jeanne,

00:20.771 --> 00:22.314
and from my first marriage,

00:22.397 --> 00:24.149
Marie Delphine Lopez.

00:24.233 --> 00:25.817
But everyone calls her Borquita.

00:26.944 --> 00:28.403
What they may lack in outer beauty,

00:28.487 --> 00:30.906
they more than make up for
with their many talents.

00:30.989 --> 00:33.033
Borquita is a huge help to me
with the domestics.

00:33.450 --> 00:36.537
While Jeanne excels in petit point.

00:36.620 --> 00:38.247
My youngest, Pauline,

00:38.330 --> 00:41.959
well, her major talent
has yet to reveal itself. (CHUCKLES)

00:42.626 --> 00:44.670
Perhaps my talent is in the boudoir,

00:45.379 --> 00:46.505
Mother dear.

00:48.465 --> 00:51.260
I guess we'll find out
on your wedding night, <i>mon petit.</i>

01:27.588 --> 01:29.006
MAN: <i>Mon cherie.</i>

01:30.048 --> 01:31.258
When the blood dries,

01:31.341 --> 01:34.011
my skin is supposed to be tight as a drum.

01:35.179 --> 01:37.181
Just look at this wattle.

01:39.933 --> 01:42.352
(SNIFFS) This blood's not fresh.

01:42.436 --> 01:43.770
Borquita!

01:45.105 --> 01:46.398
(SPEAKING IN CREOLE)

01:46.648 --> 01:49.443
<i>Mon cherie,</i> something's happened
during the dinner party.

01:54.990 --> 01:56.408
Stupid slut!

01:56.491 --> 02:01.997
I invite all the eligible bachelors
just to meet you and you...

02:02.080 --> 02:05.000
-(SLAPPING)
-Spread your filthy legs for the houseman!

02:05.375 --> 02:07.586
You might as well rut with the family dog!

02:07.878 --> 02:09.671
You can't control me, Mother.

02:09.755 --> 02:10.756
The hell I can't!

02:11.131 --> 02:12.591
The hell I can't.

02:12.758 --> 02:14.843
You know what we're going to say?

02:14.927 --> 02:17.638
We're going to say he took you by force.

02:17.721 --> 02:19.181
Like the savage he is.

02:19.515 --> 02:21.600
No, ma'am, I did no such thing.

02:21.683 --> 02:23.352
-Yes, that's what happened.
-Miss Pauline came on to me.

02:23.435 --> 02:25.521
And I told her I belong to someone else.

02:25.604 --> 02:27.648
Keep that mongrel quiet.

02:28.649 --> 02:29.858
(BASTIEN CRIES OUT)

02:31.485 --> 02:32.986
Haul him upstairs.

02:33.487 --> 02:34.780
BASTIEN: No. No.

02:35.155 --> 02:36.198
No.

02:36.281 --> 02:37.282
(HINGES CREAKING)

02:37.366 --> 02:38.575
(DOOR THUDS)

02:41.328 --> 02:42.663
<i>Bonsoir,</i> my pets.

02:43.455 --> 02:44.665
Did y'all miss me?

02:44.748 --> 02:46.250
(MUFFLED SHOUTS)

02:47.751 --> 02:48.877
Hush up.

02:48.961 --> 02:52.047
Or I'll rip your lips open
and stuff more shit in there.

02:53.507 --> 02:55.342
-Why?
-(CHAINS RATTLING)

02:55.425 --> 02:56.927
Why are you doing this to us?

02:57.594 --> 02:58.971
Because I can?

03:00.430 --> 03:01.431
Oh, <i>merde.</i>

03:01.515 --> 03:03.392
Now we gonna have flies up here.

03:05.185 --> 03:06.562
(CHAINS RATTLING)

03:07.563 --> 03:08.772
There.

03:09.857 --> 03:11.275
That should do it.

03:11.358 --> 03:12.526
Bastien.

03:12.943 --> 03:13.944
(GROANING)

03:14.027 --> 03:16.113
You want to rut like a beast...

03:16.196 --> 03:18.490
Then we're going to treat you like one.

03:18.699 --> 03:20.117
(SOBBING)

03:20.492 --> 03:22.578
Where's my pickaninny with the head?

03:31.920 --> 03:33.839
(BASTIEN WHIMPERING FRANTICALLY)

03:37.843 --> 03:38.886
Put it on him.

03:39.469 --> 03:41.221
(FRANTIC WHIMPERING CONTINUES)

03:54.776 --> 03:57.487
Darling, you have outdone yourself.

03:57.571 --> 03:59.489
However did you think this up?

03:59.948 --> 04:02.910
My great literacy began
with Greek mythology.

04:03.744 --> 04:05.454
I used to sit on Daddy's lap

04:05.537 --> 04:07.623
and he would read me those stories

04:07.998 --> 04:09.958
full of their vengeful Gods

04:10.042 --> 04:13.128
and wondrous miraculous creatures.

04:13.921 --> 04:16.632
But the Minotaur was always my favorite.

04:17.758 --> 04:20.552
Half-man, half-bull.

04:21.261 --> 04:22.262
(BASTIEN WHIMPERING FRANTICALLY)

04:22.346 --> 04:23.347
And now...

04:23.972 --> 04:26.517
I have one of my very own.

04:26.600 --> 04:28.477
(BASTIEN CONTINUES WHIMPERING)

04:36.527 --> 04:38.529
(THEME MUSIC PLAYING)

05:53.437 --> 05:54.646
(KEYS JINGLING)

05:58.775 --> 06:00.027
Are you sure about this?

06:00.485 --> 06:02.863
Come on. My mom gets home at 6:00.

06:36.605 --> 06:38.315
It just sucks being somebody's first.

06:39.399 --> 06:40.901
I don't want to hurt you.

06:42.528 --> 06:43.612
I'll be okay.

06:52.329 --> 06:53.413
Are you okay?

06:54.122 --> 06:55.123
Yeah.

07:02.256 --> 07:03.340
Charlie?

07:06.552 --> 07:07.553
Charlie?

07:07.636 --> 07:08.720
Charlie, Charlie, what's wrong?

07:08.804 --> 07:10.430
-(GRUNTING)
-Charlie!

07:10.931 --> 07:11.932
Charlie!

07:13.225 --> 07:14.309
(TRAIN HORN BLARES)

07:17.980 --> 07:21.942
ZOE: <i>It's a cliche,</i>
<i>but like all cliches, it's the truth.</i>

07:22.401 --> 07:24.027
<i>Your life can change overnight.</i>

07:24.111 --> 07:25.445
<i>Or in a moment.</i>

07:26.446 --> 07:27.573
(SIGHS)

07:27.656 --> 07:30.409
<i>The official word on Charlie's death</i>
<i>was a brain aneurysm.</i>

07:30.492 --> 07:33.245
<i>But the doctors had never seen anything</i>
<i>quite like it before.</i>

07:33.745 --> 07:35.122
<i>The blood...</i>

07:35.205 --> 07:36.456
<i>All that blood.</i>

07:37.291 --> 07:39.042
It's not your fault, baby.

07:40.210 --> 07:41.336
It's ours.

07:42.421 --> 07:46.550
There's something
I should have told you a long time ago.

07:46.633 --> 07:48.218
I prayed it would skip your generation.

07:49.887 --> 07:54.308
Your great-grandmother
had the same genetic affliction.

07:54.725 --> 07:56.435
ZOE: <i>So apparently I'm a witch.</i>

07:56.935 --> 07:58.770
<i>It runs in my family,</i>
<i>but it doesn't show up</i>

07:58.854 --> 08:00.689
<i>in every generation, or in every girl.</i>

08:01.148 --> 08:03.650
<i>Like my cousin Amanda,</i>
<i>she's just bulimic.</i>

08:03.734 --> 08:06.862
<i>We read about the Salem Witch Trials</i>
<i>in like, fifth grade.</i>

08:06.945 --> 08:08.530
<i>Guess I should have paid more attention.</i>

08:08.614 --> 08:11.533
CROWD: Hang her!
Drown her! Burn her!

08:11.617 --> 08:13.493
CHIEF MAGISTRATE: Mercy Osbourne,

08:13.577 --> 08:15.829
you have been sentenced to death.

08:15.913 --> 08:18.373
May God have mercy
on your wretched soul.

08:18.749 --> 08:20.667
ZOE: <i>Those girls weren't even witches.</i>

08:20.751 --> 08:22.920
<i>The real witches were cunning</i>
<i>and careful not to be caught.</i>

08:23.003 --> 08:25.005
(CROWD SHOUTING)

08:25.088 --> 08:27.216
<i>In fact after that,</i>
<i>they got the hell out of Dodge.</i>

08:27.299 --> 08:28.342
-(CROWD SHOUTING)
<i>-They fled.</i>

08:28.425 --> 08:29.676
<i>As far South as they could.</i>

08:30.385 --> 08:32.638
(CROWD SHOUTING)

08:32.971 --> 08:35.641
<i>That's how eventually New Orleans</i>
<i>became the new Salem.</i>

08:35.724 --> 08:37.309
WOMAN: <i>There's a school there.</i>

08:38.227 --> 08:40.395
A boarding school for girls like you.

08:41.813 --> 08:43.106
You'll be safe.

08:43.815 --> 08:45.025
You're sending me away?

08:45.108 --> 08:47.110
WOMAN: I'm sorry, baby.

08:47.194 --> 08:48.612
We can't keep you here anymore.

08:49.029 --> 08:50.155
It's too dangerous.

08:54.868 --> 08:55.869
What's going on?

08:56.161 --> 08:57.829
Mom, what's going on? What is this?

08:57.913 --> 09:01.583
Mom! Mom... No, what is this?
Mom...

09:02.209 --> 09:04.253
(SOBBING) Mom!

09:06.630 --> 09:08.549
We'll handle it from here.

09:09.174 --> 09:10.926
Can't I drive her to the station?

09:11.009 --> 09:13.387
She's our daughter now, Nora.

09:13.470 --> 09:15.138
You've done all you can.

09:15.222 --> 09:18.267
A long good-bye
would only make things worse.

09:19.101 --> 09:21.061
By the way, these drapes.

09:21.144 --> 09:23.897
I'm just mad for tartan.

10:03.645 --> 10:06.273
(DOORBELL CHIMES)

10:06.356 --> 10:07.941
(METALLIC CLICK)

10:08.025 --> 10:09.443
(HINGES CREAKING)

10:26.084 --> 10:27.878
(HINGES CREAKING)

10:35.219 --> 10:36.637
Hello?

10:36.720 --> 10:38.222
(HINGES CREAKING)

10:44.228 --> 10:45.312
Hello?

10:46.855 --> 10:48.065
Hello?

10:50.901 --> 10:52.569
(FLAMES CRACKLING)

11:41.618 --> 11:42.661
(SCREAMS)

11:43.495 --> 11:45.080
(RUNNING FOOTSTEPS)

11:45.163 --> 11:46.331
(ZOE GASPING)

11:48.041 --> 11:49.168
(SCREAMS)

11:55.674 --> 11:58.677
O dark father,
we offer this flesh up to you,

11:58.760 --> 12:00.095
blood, life, and all.

12:00.179 --> 12:01.680
Get the hell off me!

12:03.807 --> 12:05.392
-(PANTING)
-Jesus,

12:05.475 --> 12:07.186
Sabrina, relax.

12:07.436 --> 12:08.478
We're just messing with you.

12:09.521 --> 12:10.689
Holy shit. Are you...

12:10.772 --> 12:12.983
Madison Montgomery, movie star.

12:13.066 --> 12:14.359
Shit.

12:14.443 --> 12:15.819
When's the last time
you made a movie, girl?

12:15.903 --> 12:16.987
I'm Nan. Hi.

12:17.070 --> 12:18.071
Zoe.

12:18.155 --> 12:19.156
Queenie.

12:19.239 --> 12:20.282
So bored now.

12:20.699 --> 12:21.783
So, is this all of you?

12:21.867 --> 12:23.243
CORDELIA: At the moment.

12:25.746 --> 12:28.165
Cordelia Foxx, Headmistress.

12:29.166 --> 12:32.085
All right, girls, there's a van
full of groceries in the driveway

12:32.169 --> 12:33.378
that needs unloading.

12:33.462 --> 12:36.465
I'll show Zoe to her room.
Then we meet for Midday Gathering.

12:36.548 --> 12:37.758
Let's go.

12:44.806 --> 12:47.559
CORDELIA: <i>Miss Robichaux's Academy</i>
<i>for Exceptional Young Ladies</i>

12:47.643 --> 12:49.770
<i>was established</i>
<i>as a premiere girls' finishing school</i>

12:49.853 --> 12:51.355
<i>in 1790.</i>

12:51.939 --> 12:55.692
<i>During the Civil War,</i>
<i>it was converted</i><i>into a military hospital.</i>

12:55.776 --> 12:58.445
<i>Afterwards, it came under</i>
<i>new management.</i>

12:58.862 --> 13:00.155
<i>Our management.</i>

13:00.531 --> 13:03.659
<i>In 1868, Marianne Wharton,</i>

13:03.742 --> 13:06.036
<i>a prominent East Coast society matron,</i>

13:06.119 --> 13:07.538
<i>early suffragette...</i>

13:07.621 --> 13:09.915
<i>Author of several popular</i>
<i>children's books...</i>

13:09.998 --> 13:13.502
And, as it happened,
the reigning Supreme of that time...

13:13.585 --> 13:17.256
<i>Purchased this facility,</i>
<i>retaining the name as a cover,</i>

13:17.339 --> 13:18.841
<i>establishing a safe haven</i>

13:18.924 --> 13:21.051
<i>where young witches</i>
<i>could gather to learn.</i>

13:23.178 --> 13:24.304
<i>In its heyday,</i>

13:24.388 --> 13:27.683
<i>the academy was home</i>
<i>to as many as 60 girls.</i>

13:28.267 --> 13:30.519
<i>Over the years,</i>
<i>those numbers dwindled.</i>

13:30.811 --> 13:32.020
ZOE: <i>Why?</i>

13:32.104 --> 13:33.981
We're a dying breed, Zoe.

13:34.064 --> 13:36.441
Many of the families
who knew they carried the bloodline

13:36.525 --> 13:38.360
made a choice not to reproduce.

13:38.777 --> 13:40.070
So, what's a Supreme?

13:40.153 --> 13:43.198
An average witch
is born with a few natural gifts.

13:43.282 --> 13:45.492
But in each generation
there is one woman

13:45.826 --> 13:48.453
who embodies countless gifts.
Some say...

13:48.537 --> 13:49.621
All of them.

13:49.705 --> 13:51.081
She is the Supreme.

13:51.498 --> 13:52.499
Are you the Supreme?

13:52.916 --> 13:54.251
(CHUCKLES)

13:55.752 --> 13:56.920
No.

13:57.004 --> 13:58.380
I'm like you.

13:58.797 --> 14:00.215
Just a witch.

14:00.674 --> 14:03.677
And a teacher.
I'm here to help you identify your gifts

14:03.760 --> 14:05.345
and teach you how to control them.

14:05.429 --> 14:06.930
She means to suppress them.

14:07.014 --> 14:08.432
Not suppression.

14:09.141 --> 14:10.142
Control.

14:10.225 --> 14:11.685
She thinks it's still the 1600s.

14:11.768 --> 14:12.811
No.

14:12.895 --> 14:15.939
Back then, our kind
understood the dangers.

14:16.023 --> 14:20.485
<i>Today, so many families</i>
<i>know nothing of their ancestry.</i>

14:20.569 --> 14:23.238
<i>Too many girls aren't lucky enough</i>
<i>to have found us</i>

14:23.322 --> 14:26.491
<i>or weren't identified in time</i>
<i>for us to have found them.</i>

14:26.575 --> 14:28.035
<i>Like that poor Cajun girl</i>

14:28.118 --> 14:30.329
<i>just outside Lafayette</i>
<i>a few months back.</i>

14:31.455 --> 14:32.915
<i>Misty Day.</i>

14:33.290 --> 14:35.584
<i>She wasn't much older</i>
<i>than any of you.</i>

14:35.667 --> 14:39.004
<i>And she had a gift,</i>
<i>the power of resurgence.</i>

14:39.087 --> 14:41.215
MAN: You'll only be saved
by the word of God...

14:43.050 --> 14:45.844
<i>Misty could reach into that place</i>
<i>between life and death</i>

14:45.928 --> 14:47.804
<i>and draw a soul back</i>
<i>from the precipice,</i>

14:48.305 --> 14:50.516
<i>back to this side, back to life.</i>

14:50.599 --> 14:51.683
It's dark magic!

14:52.434 --> 14:56.188
<i>To some, this appeared to be</i>
<i>the God-touched power of resurrection.</i>

14:56.271 --> 14:59.608
To cast you in to darkness and sin!

14:59.691 --> 15:02.528
<i>To others, necromancy.</i>

15:02.903 --> 15:06.323
To cast you
into separation from God!

15:08.617 --> 15:09.910
So what happened to her?

15:10.285 --> 15:11.620
The same thing that's happened

15:11.703 --> 15:13.830
to women like us
throughout the centuries.

15:13.914 --> 15:15.207
(PANTS) Let me go!

15:15.791 --> 15:16.792
Let me go!

15:17.376 --> 15:18.377
(SOBS)

15:19.253 --> 15:21.004
(COUGHING)

15:24.216 --> 15:25.676
(WHIMPERING)

15:31.056 --> 15:32.516
(PANTING)

15:33.475 --> 15:36.311
It's you that will end in flames.
I swear it!

15:37.855 --> 15:39.231
(CRYING)

15:41.108 --> 15:42.693
(WAILING)

15:44.987 --> 15:46.697
We are under siege, ladies.

15:47.114 --> 15:48.156
Our lives,

15:48.615 --> 15:49.992
our very existence

15:50.576 --> 15:51.994
is always at risk.

15:52.077 --> 15:55.038
Know this or face extinction.

16:11.430 --> 16:13.182
(THUNDER RUMBLES SOFTLY)

16:17.227 --> 16:18.520
This is Allegra.

16:20.856 --> 16:24.401
She is the equivalent
of a human female in her late 80s.

16:25.402 --> 16:28.405
Allegra suffers
from acute bradycardia,

16:28.488 --> 16:29.948
her kidneys are failing,

16:30.032 --> 16:32.284
she's lost the ability to swallow.

16:33.410 --> 16:36.246
Allegra, in short, is dying.

16:37.706 --> 16:41.126
Now, several hours
after this video was taken,

16:41.210 --> 16:44.671
we injected Allegra
with our Serum RM47.

16:45.839 --> 16:48.592
We expanded on
the University of Wisconsin studies

16:48.675 --> 16:51.094
on induced pluripotent stem cells.

16:53.180 --> 16:55.224
Meet Allegra today.

17:03.774 --> 17:04.942
I'll have what she's having.

17:05.275 --> 17:07.402
(CHUCKLES) And you will.

17:07.986 --> 17:09.363
Sooner than you'd think.

17:09.780 --> 17:13.075
We should be ready for human trials
in two years' time.

17:13.408 --> 17:14.409
This afternoon.

17:14.493 --> 17:16.537
-(CHUCKLES)
-Preferably in the next half hour.

17:16.620 --> 17:17.955
I have a dinner engagement.

17:18.038 --> 17:21.041
I'm sorry, but, uh...
Well, that's impossible.

17:21.583 --> 17:23.877
I hear you like to get

17:23.961 --> 17:26.380
sauced at biochemistry conventions

17:26.463 --> 17:29.174
and brag about
how you're gonna win the Nobel Prize

17:29.258 --> 17:30.634
for the work you're doing here,

17:30.717 --> 17:33.554
research that has been entirely funded

17:34.054 --> 17:35.722
by my late husband's money.

17:35.806 --> 17:37.516
I have made you rich,

17:39.268 --> 17:40.978
soon to be famous.

17:42.437 --> 17:43.856
I want that medicine.

17:44.314 --> 17:47.943
I paid for it, and I want it.
Now.

17:48.026 --> 17:49.736
You can't smoke in here.

17:50.779 --> 17:52.197
(EXHALES)

17:53.448 --> 17:54.533
Fiona...

17:56.034 --> 17:58.245
You are a very beautiful woman.

17:59.329 --> 18:02.124
But if you're just looking
for something cosmetic,

18:02.499 --> 18:04.168
I can recommend a plastic surgeon.

18:05.836 --> 18:07.254
What I need

18:08.839 --> 18:10.883
is an infusion of vitality.

18:11.508 --> 18:12.634
Of youth.

18:13.927 --> 18:17.055
I want that drug, David,
and I want it now.

18:19.266 --> 18:21.810
Even if I wanted to give it to you,
I couldn't.

18:22.561 --> 18:24.479
What we do here is not magic.

18:26.440 --> 18:27.441
I'm sorry.

18:31.695 --> 18:34.448
<i>(IN-A-GADDA-DA-VIDA</i> PLAYING)

18:43.707 --> 18:45.000
(SNIFFING)

18:56.595 --> 18:58.847
REPORTER: <i>Last night,</i>
<i>communities across the county</i>

18:58.931 --> 19:01.934
<i>held candlelight vigils</i>
<i>praying for Misty's safe return.</i>

19:02.017 --> 19:05.312
<i>However, sources close to the family</i>
<i>have declined to comment</i>

19:05.395 --> 19:07.064
<i>on the fact that authorities now believe</i>

19:07.147 --> 19:09.650
<i>they have found the last known location</i>
<i>of the missing girl.</i>

19:09.733 --> 19:12.361
<i>It is rumored that Misty Day</i>
<i>may have been burned at the stake,</i>

19:12.444 --> 19:14.238
<i>though no official statement</i>
<i>has been released.</i>

19:14.321 --> 19:15.405
(KNOCKING)

19:20.577 --> 19:23.121
You made me leave
my daughters' violin recital early.

19:23.205 --> 19:27.334
You've been injecting me
with your shit for five days now

19:27.417 --> 19:29.086
and nothing...

19:29.419 --> 19:31.505
Nothing has changed.

19:32.589 --> 19:36.510
How do I know you're not just
shooting me up with some sugar water?

19:36.593 --> 19:39.680
I have risked my career
giving you these drugs.

19:39.763 --> 19:41.557
They could kill you.
I could go to jail.

19:42.307 --> 19:43.433
Double the dosage.

19:43.517 --> 19:44.601
Pull our funding.

19:44.685 --> 19:45.769
Give me more!

19:45.853 --> 19:47.688
We are organic matter.

19:47.771 --> 19:49.314
We are animals. We rot,

19:49.398 --> 19:50.858
we die!

19:54.403 --> 19:56.697
I will tender my resignation
in the morning.

